Step 1: Install Terraform
On your machine (Ubuntu for example):
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y wget unzip

wget https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/1.8.5/terraform_1.8.5_linux_amd64.zip
unzip terraform_1.8.5_linux_amd64.zip
sudo mv terraform /usr/local/bin/
terraform -version

Step 2: Configure AWS CLI
Make sure you have AWS credentials set up:aws configure


Provide:
AWS Access Key ID


AWS Secret Access Key


Default region (e.g. us-east-1)


Default output: json



Step 3: Create Terraform project
Make a project folder:
mkdir terraform-ec2 && cd terraform-ec2

Inside, create main.tf
nano :
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-2"
}

resource "aws_instance" "wa_ec2" {
  ami           = "ami-0c55b159cbfafe1f0" # Amazon Linux 2 AMI (update with your region)
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  # Use existing VPC + Subnet
  subnet_id              = "subnet-0123456789abcdef0" # <-- replace with your subnet ID
  vpc_security_group_ids = ["sg-0123456789abcdef0"]   # <-- replace with your security group ID

  key_name = "my-keypair" # <-- replace with your AWS key pair name

  tags = {
    Name = "MyTerraformEC2"
  }
}

 Step 4: Initialize Terraform
terraform init

 Step 5: Plan infrastructure
terraform plan

This will show what Terraform is going to create.
 Step 6: Apply to create EC2
terraform apply -auto-approve

Terraform will create the EC2 instance ðŸŽ‰

Step 7: Destroy when done
To avoid AWS costs:
terraform destroy -auto-approve


Things you need:
VPC ID â†’ not directly needed, since Subnet is already inside a VPC.


Subnet ID â†’ copy from AWS Console (EC2 â†’ Subnets).


Security Group ID â†’ copy from AWS Console (VPC â†’ Security Groups).


Key Pair Name â†’ create in EC2 Console if not already (used for SSH login).


 Deploy
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply -auto-approve

This will launch your EC2 inside your existing VPC & Subnet, using your own security group and key pair.
Do you want me to also add a Security Group creation inside Terraform, or you prefer always using existing security groups from AWS Console?



